reason.tex:
\textbf{The standard result is} \\
			\begin{align}
			  \int\dfrac{dx}{x^2 + b^2} &= \dfrac{1}{b}\tan^{-1}\dfrac{x}{b} \\
			  \therefore\text{ if } a &\gt 0,\text{ then } a = b^2. \\
			  \implies\int\dfrac{dx}{x^2+a} &= \int\dfrac{dx}{x^2 + b^2} 
			  = \dfrac{1}{b}\tan^{-1}\dfrac{x}{b} + C \\
			  &= \dfrac{1}{\sqrt{a}}\tan^{-1}\dfrac{x}{\sqrt{a}} + C
			\end{align}
